p/1680502549\"},{\"title\":\"Domain Modeling Made Functional: Tackle Software SPlexity with Domain-Driven Design and F# by Scott Wlaschin | Goodreads\",\"url\":\"https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/34921689\"},{\"title\":\"#79 - Domain-Driven Design With Functional Programming - Scott Wlaschin - Tech Lead Journal\",\"url\":\"https://techleadjournal.dev/episodes/79/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Scott Wlaschin's \"Domain Modeling Made Functional\" and his type-driven design philosophy:\n\n## Overview\n\nScott Wlaschin is the author of \"Domain Modeling Made Functional\" and the popular F# site fsharpforfunandprofit.com. This book is the first to combine DDD with techniques from statically typed functional programming.\n\n## Type-Driven Design Philosophy\n\nThe core of Wlaschin's philosophy centers on using types as a design and validation tool:\n\n- Types can be used to represent the domain in a fine-grained, self documenting way. And in many cases, types can even be used to encode business rules so that you literally cannot create incorrect code.\n\n- Model a complex domain accurately using the F# type system, creating compilable code that is also readable documentation—ensuring that the code and design never get out of sync.\n\n- The author shows how to model the domain using only types and functions.\n\n## Key Approach\n\nDomain-driven design (DDD) combined with functional programming is presented as an innovative approach that can result in software designs that model real-world requirements both elegantly and concisely—often more so than an object-oriented approach.\n\nThe search results provided are from various time periods (with one review dated April 2025), but they don't reveal significant new developments or changes to his philosophy specifically in 2024-2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"c830e6d2-9801-4a3d-adcc-6e41e22ddba9","timesta