er) 1, Krug, Steve, eBook - Amazon.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.amazon.com/Rocket-Surgery-Made-Easy-Yourself-ebook/dp/B002UXRGNO\"},{\"title\":\"Rocket Surgery Made Easy: The Do-It-Yourself Guide to Finding and Fixing Usability Problems by Steve Krug, Paperback | Barnes & Noble®\",\"url\":\"https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/rocket-surgery-made-easy-steve-krug/1100293650\"},{\"title\":\"Steve Krug | Usability, mostly.\",\"url\":\"https://sensible.com/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Steve Krug's \"Rocket Surgery Made Easy\" and usability testing:\n\n## Overview\n\n\"Rocket Surgery is a how-to book for doing your own usability tests. In 168 pages, it explains everything you need to know to conduct tests.\" In this how-to companion to Don't Make Me Think: A Common Sense Approach to Web Usability, Steve Krug spells out a streamlined approach to usability testing that anyone can easily apply to their own Web site, application, or other product.\n\n## Core Philosophy\n\nRocket Surgery is about how to do usability. It's a how-to book that shows you how to do your own simple, fast, effective usability tests. The approach emphasizes simplicity and accessibility—Krug outlines the core principles of usability testing, emphasizing its simplicity and cost-effectiveness, stressing that usability testing doesn't have to be a complex, expensive endeavor, and can be conducted by anyone with a basic understanding of the process.\n\n## Key Recommendations\n\n\"Do It Yourself Usability Testing\" since it's supposed to be cheap, easy-to-do and takes just a morning a month. Krug discusses the process of acting on test results, emphasizing the importance of quick, iterative improvements. He suggests fixing the most critical issues first and then retesting the product to ensure the effectiveness of the changes, and highlights the value of continuous testing throughout the development process.\n\nThe search results mainly cover information about the book itself rather than recent activity, as the book was published in 2010 and remains a foundational text in UX/usability practice.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"c7aff48f-e9dc-4268-83bb-56d53aa9f8a7","timestamp":"2026-02-08T18:44:16.259Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"14ee2893-848a-489b-a668-523687fdf418"}
{"parentUuid":"8b66b114-d470-495f-adaf-9ab56e2660da","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"2ac9b335-ecf3-4e43-a8c4-e750faf9e881","version":"2.1.37","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"affc159","slug":"cached-toasting-simon","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CYhUXJyLEqMJfshUTJXXT3","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Marty Cagan \"TRANSFORMED\" 2024 product operating model principles philosophy\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Moving To The Product Operating Model by Marty Cagan\",\"url\":\"https://userpilot.com/blog/moving-to-the-product-operating-model-by-marty-cagan/\"},{\"title\":\"Marty Cagan on TRANSFORMED: Moving to the Product Operating Model\",\"url\":\"https://www.news.aakashg.com/p/transformed-product-operating-model-marty-cagan\"},{\"title\":\"The Product Operating Model Explained: From Pilot Teams to Full Transformation\",\"url\":\"https://www.producttalk.org/the-product-operating-model/\"},{\"title\":\"Transformed: Moving to the Product Operating Model (Silicon Valley Product Group): Cagan, Marty, Hickman, Lea, Jones, Chris, Idiodi, Christian, Moore, John: 9781119697336: Amazon.com: Books\",\"url\":\"https://www.amazon.com/Transformed-Becoming-Product-Driven-Company-Silicon/dp/1119697336\"},{\"title\":\"TRANSFORMED: Moving to the Product Operating Model - Silicon Valley Product Group : Silicon Valley Product Group\",\"url\":\"https://www.svpg.com/books/transformed-moving-to-the-product-operating-model/\"},{\"title\":\"TRANSFORMED: Moving to the Product Operating Model with Marty Cagan | by Paweł Huryn | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://huryn.medium.com/transformed-moving-to-the-product-operating-model-with-marty-cagan-6f1489669347\"},{\"title\":\"Product Operating Model Principles\",\"url\":\"https://www.lifeintech.com/2024/08/22/product-operating-model-principles/\"},{\"title\":\"Transformed: Moving to the Product Operating Model - Marty Cagan, Lea Hickman, Chris Jones, Christian Idiodi, John Moore - Google Books\",\"url\":\"https://books.google.com/books/about/Transformed.html?id=RLruEAAAQBAJ\"},{\"title\":\"Marty Cagan on the Product Operating Model and Scrum's ...\",\"url\":\"https://age-of-product.com/marty-cagan-product-operating-model/\"},{\"title\":\"Product Model First Principles In Depth: Product Team and Product Strategy\",\"url\":\"https://www.productcompass.pm/p/product-model-first-principles-transformed-cagan\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Marty Cagan's \"TRANSFORMED\" book and the product operating model principles and philosophy:\n\n## Overview\n\nTRANSFORMED: Moving to the Product Operating Model answers how to actually transition to the product operating model, guiding you in assessing your current situation, understanding where you want to be, and planning a path to transformation. The product operating model is not a particular process or methodology or single way of working; it is a set of principles that you'll find in those companies that believe they should be powering their business with technology.\n\n## Core Philosophy\n\nWhile each of these companies has its own unique product culture, they all share the same fundamental principles. The product operating model is about consistently creating technology-powered solutions that deliver value to customers and that also drive results for the business. It's about achieving outcomes versus merely producing output.\n\n## Key Principles\n\nThe book outlines 20 product model first principles shared by the best product companies. These include:\n\n- The most fundamental of all product concepts is the notion of an empowered, cross-functional product team. Product teams must be given a problem to solve, rather than solutions to build, and, most importantly, are held accountable for the results.\n\n- Establish outcome-based goals, leveraging Objectives and Key Results (OKRs), which create focus on the priority, promote curiosity and provide relevant context. Outcomes are the results of actions, not features.\n\n- One of the product model's first principles is innovation over predictability, and another is principles over process.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"59cb1691-6b4c-4678-9974-84f18ed9f1b5","timestamp":"2026-02-08T18:44:16.605Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8b66b114-d470-495f-adaf-9ab56e2660da"}
