{"parentUuid":"8ef295d7-1057-45ee-bcf2-1e46b454b1c0","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"2ac9b335-ecf3-4e43-a8c4-e750faf9e881","version":"2.1.37","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"affc159","slug":"cached-toasting-simon","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Xn6TZxiQKBgTWt5d99P6f","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Kent Beck \"Tidy First?\" 2024 2025 TDD software design thinking\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Design in TDD - by Kent Beck - Software Design: Tidy First?\",\"url\":\"https://tidyfirst.substack.com/p/design-in-tdd\"},{\"title\":\"Canon TDD - by Kent Beck - Software Design: Tidy First?\",\"url\":\"https://tidyfirst.substack.com/p/canon-tdd\"},{\"title\":\"SE Radio 615: Kent Beck on “Tidy First?” – Software Engineering Radio\",\"url\":\"https://se-radio.net/2024/05/se-radio-615-kent-beck-on-tidy-first/\"},{\"title\":\"Kent Beck - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kent_Beck\"},{\"title\":\"Kent Beck - Software Design Pioneer, Author, Artist & Musician\",\"url\":\"https://kentbeck.com/\"},{\"title\":\"TDD Outcomes - by Kent Beck - Software Design: Tidy First?\",\"url\":\"https://tidyfirst.substack.com/p/tdd-outcomes\"},{\"title\":\"Tidy First?: A Personal Exercise in Empirical Software Design: Beck, Kent: 9781098151249: Amazon.com: Books\",\"url\":\"https://www.amazon.com/Tidy-First-Personal-Exercise-Empirical/dp/1098151240\"},{\"title\":\"Software Design: Tidy First? | Kent Beck | Substack\",\"url\":\"https://tidyfirst.substack.com/\"},{\"title\":\"Founder Call Friday, 7 June 2024, 0830 PDT - by Kent Beck\",\"url\":\"https://tidyfirst.substack.com/p/founder-call-friday-7-june-2024-0830\"},{\"title\":\"TDD Isn't Design - by Kent Beck\",\"url\":\"https://tidyfirst.substack.com/p/tdd-isnt-design\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Kent Beck's recent work on \"Tidy First?\" TDD, and software design:\n\n## Recent Publications and Focus\n\nKent Beck published \"Tidy First? A Personal Exercise in Empirical Design,\" the first book in a series on Empirical Software Design. He is currently working on the third book in the series, \"Tidy Together,\" about teams practicing software design together as they continue to develop features.\n\n## TDD and Design Relationship\n\nBeck has been actively clarifying the relationship between TDD and software design in 2024-2025. He emphasizes that tidying first is not part of the TDD workflow, as TDD is very specific. In his recent writings, when applying TDD, Beck notes points that remind him to design, including thinking about \"What is the design which, if I had had it, would have made that implementation easier?\" after getting a test running.\n\n## Canon TDD Clarification\n\nBeck defines Test-Driven Development as a programming workflow where a programmer needs to change behavior of a system, with TDD intended to help create a new state where everything that used to work still works, the new behavior works as expected, the system is ready for the next change, and the programmer feels confident.\n\n## Recent Speaking and Newsletter Activity\n\nBeck recently spoke at the O'Reilly \"Coding with AI\" seminar in May 2025, presenting \"Vibe Coding: More Experiments, More Care\". His newsletter, Tidy First, gives paying subscribers instant access to chapters as he drafts them.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"fae05989-f392-47f4-bf7d-115f2763bfcf","timestamp":"2026-02-08T18:43:55.651Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8ef295d7-1057-45ee-bcf2-1e46b454b1c0"}
