ow/episodes/Carson-Gross-Creator-of-HTMX-Reflects-on-Hypermedia-Systems-e2vlq26\"},{\"title\":\"Hypermedia Systems 1, Gross, Carson, Stepinski, Adam, Akşimşek , Deniz, Talcott, William, Amundsen, Mike, eBook - Amazon.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.amazon.com/Hypermedia-Systems-Carson-Gross-ebook/dp/B0CC315VJK\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Carson Gross, HTMX, and his \"Hypermedia Systems\" philosophy:\n\n## About Carson Gross and HTMX\n\nCarson Gross is the creator of a JavaScript framework called htmx. HTMX—or, \"hypertext markup extensions\"—provides an attributes-based approach for adding rich interactivity to your web application.\n\n## Hypermedia Systems Philosophy\n\nThe \"Hypermedia Systems\" book explores a simpler approach to building applications on the Web and beyond with htmx and Hyperview, two technologies that embrace hypermedia as a system architecture.\n\nThe entire first section of the book covers the history of the web, the concept of hypermedia as a unified interface, the true and original meaning of REST (REpresentational State Transfer), and makes the argument that HTML and HATEOS (Hypermedia as the Engine of Application State) has many advantages over the extremely tight coupling required by today's Single-Page Application (SPA) frameworks.\n\n## Core Philosophy of HTMX\n\nThe core philosophy of \"HTML as the interface\" and how hypermedia principles influenced HTMX's design is central to his work. Any element can issue any type of request in response to any event, and it can place the response content anywhere in the DOM, which Gross says completes HTML as a hypermedia.\n\n## Recent Activity (2024-2025)\n\nCarson Gross and Alex Petros discuss htmx's future direction and philosophy, explaining how the project aims to emulate jQuery's success through API stability, minimal feature additions, and quarterly releases while continuing to promote hypermedia-driven development. Carson Gross talks about its evolution from intercooler.js, its viral rise on social media, and its philosophy of simplicity and stability.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"227143e7-fa99-465a-82e8-2de1dd89706d","timestamp":"2026-02-08T18:43:58.335Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"fd7fe197-7f42-4872-8ff1-00aec7c62d6f"}
