hnologies:\n\n## About Luca Palmieri and Mainmatter\n\nLuca Palmieri is a Principal Engineering Consultant at Mainmatter. He is best known as the author of \"Zero to Production in Rust\", an introduction to using Rust for backend development and \"100 Exercises To Learn Rust\", a hands-on course by Mainmatter.\n\n## Pavex Framework\n\nLuca started working on a new web framework for Rust called pavex, with the goal of great ergonomics and high performance - no sacrifices. Pavex is significantly different as it sees itself as a specialized compiler for building Rust APIs.\n\nThe framework uses pavex_cli, a transpiler designed specifically for web applications, which generates the source code for web servers using straight-forward Rust. The generated code contains no indirection - no runtime reflection, no dynamic dispatch, no type-maps. It's just a bunch of functions that call each other, passing around the instances they need. It's a zero-cost abstraction: you would get the same performance if you had written the code by hand.\n\n## Public Presentation and Recognition\n\nLuca introduced and demonstrated Pavex at Rust Nation 2024. Pavex is described as a new Rust framework for building APIs that addresses shortcomings in the current ecosystems.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"17b13635-4b22-4fb7-b8ac-3fd9413de503","timestamp":"2026-02-08T18:44:11.705Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f81d7e17-37e6-449f-a15e-187d666a9a43"}
